OL,6,FAt the Commonwealth summit in Samoa `
OL,7,Fthe King's first as head of the
OL,8,FCommonwealth ` Charles met leaders
OL,9,Ffrom countries who are still calling
OL,10,Ffor reparations for the wrongs of the
OL,11,Ftransatlantic slave trade.
OL,13,F"Diversity of culture, ethnicity and
OL,14,Ffaith", he said, "provides strength,
OL,15,Fnot weakness."
OL,17,FHis listening theme tied together
OL,18,Fhistory and the present when he said:
OL,19,F"through listening, we learn to
OL,20,Frespect our differences, to defeat
OL,21,Fprejudice."
